@section inLegato Legato Installation Packages

Legato Beta contains the following installation files:
- @b Legato-Toolchain-mdm9x15-14.1-x86_64.tar.bz2 - complete cross toolchain to compile Legato applications on a 64-bit Linux host.

- @b Legato-Toolchain-mdm9x15-14.1-i686.tar.bz2 - complete cross toolchain to compile Legato applications on a 32-bit Linux host.

- @b Legato-Linux-Source-mdm9x15-14.1.tar.bz2 - Legato source code with all Yocto recipes and kernel source to build Legato Linux images for AR7 and WP7 devices. 
The Poky build tool with the meta-OpenEmbedded layer is available from the Yocto project.

- @b Legato-Linux-Images-mdm9x15-14.1.tar.bz2 - prebuilt images of the Linux kernel and rootfs that match the image on the device. These can be flashed using the fastboot tool.

- @b Drivers - all the Windows drivers needed to recover your device.

- <b>One-click tools</b> - one-click firmware packages that will reinstall software from the factory onto dev kit devices. 
Itâ€™s run on Windows and requires Sierra Wireless drivers be installed.

